Afrobeats songstress Simi reacted after a scantily dressed dancer jumped on her husband Adekunle Gold while on stage. AG baby recently performed in Kampala, which happened to be Uganda’s biggest uptown Concert of 2022 featuring South African singer and Dancer Costa Titch with Uganda’s finest entertainers. It attracted tens of revellers filling up the Cricket Oval, one of the biggest concert venues in the country. However, while Adekunle Gold was performing on stage, a Ugandan girl jumped on him but he struggled against holding her which made her fall.   Yemi Alade eulogises Ada Ameh, shares video shoot     New ride confirms my big girl status – Cuppy     American record label welcomes Asake to fold   Reacting to the incident, Simi took to the comment section of her husband who had shared a shirtless post, rebuking him to go put on his shirt. The “Duduke” crooner said the lady’s action was down to him baring his chest “Dass why they’re jumping on you. Lo wo shirt e my fren,” Simi wrote. Responding, AG Baby laughed at his wife’s rebuke and assertion.